OL,3,C'Living standards are up but poorest
OL,4,Cstill more than #4,000 worse off'
OL,6,FThings are finally looking up.
OL,8,FThe headline and pay is rising faster
OL,9,Fthan prices once again.
OL,11,FThe strength of pay growth is, but the
OL,12,Fchancellor won't be fretting.
OL,14,FThe National Institute of Economic and
OL,15,FSocial Research (NIESR) calculates
OL,16,Fthat living standards are set to rise
OL,17,Fby 1.9% during 2024 - an election year.
OL,19,FBut NIESR's analysis also illustrates
OL,20,Fhow much lost ground there is still to
OL,21,Fmake up.
