OL,6,FSince 2020, the combined economic
OL,7,Fshocks of the pandemic, and , despite
OL,8,Fthe billions of pounds the government
OL,9,Fhas spent supporting households.
OL,11,FSome people have been hit harder than
OL,12,Fothers.
OL,14,FNIESR calculates that the living
OL,15,Fstandards of the 12 million households
OL,16,Fin the lowest half of the income
OL,17,Fdistribution in Britain will be
OL,18,Fbetween seven and 20% lower in 2024/
OL,19,F25, relative to 2019/20.
